	Tuple



Tuples are used to store multiple items in a single variable.
Tuples are immutable.
Tuples items are ordered, allow duplicate values.

Syntax:


1. Basic
fruits=("apple","banana","cherry")
print(fruits)

2. To find type
fruits=("apple","banana","cherry")
print(type(fruits))


3. To find length of tuple
fruits=("apple","banana","cherry")
print(len(fruits))


4. Printing from the loop
fruits=("apple","banana","cherry","mango","peach")
for i in fruits:
    print(i)


5. Printing from indexing
fruits=("apple","banana","cherry","mango","peach")
print(fruits[:4])
print(fruits[-1:])
print(fruits[:5:2])


6. Count method
	return the number of times a value occur

fruits=("apple","banana","cherry","mango","peach")
print(fruits.count("apple"))


7. Return method
	return the index of serched element


fruits=("apple","banana","cherry","mango","peach")
print(fruits.index("cherry"))



8. Modifing of the tuple by list(tuple to list, list function , then back to tuple)

fruits = ("apple", "banana", "cherry", "mango", "peach")
print(fruits)  # Original tuple

fruitl = list(fruits)  # Convert tuple to list
fruitl[1] = "grapes"   # Change "banana" to "grapes"

fruits = tuple(fruitl)  # Convert back to tuple
print(fruits)  # Updated tuple



9. Adding two tuples


fruits=("apple","banana","cherry","mango","peach")
print(fruits)

fruits2=("mango","watermelon" )
print(fruits2)

fruits+=fruits2
print(fruits)

t=fruits+fruits2
print(t)


10. Deletion of entire tuple
 
fruits=("apple","banana","cherry","mango","peach")
print(fruits)

del fruits
print(fruits)


11. Tuple packing
	Tuple packing means putting multiple values into a single tuple.

    Tuple unpacking
	Tuple unpacking means extracting values from a tuple into separate variables.


packed_tuple = 10, 20, 30, "Python"

print("Packed Tuple:", packed_tuple)
print("Type:", type(packed_tuple))

a, b, c, d = packed_tuple

print("a:", a)
print("b:", b)
print("c:", c)
print("d:", d)


